natspec.details: NFT marketplace contract that users will interact with on the Cardinal House website

cancelMarketSale(address,uint256).details: Cancels an NFT listing on the marketplace and returns the listing fee to the seller

params.itemId: the item ID of the NFT on the marketplace
params.nftContract: contract that the NFT was minted on. Only accepts Cardinal NFT contract addresses

createMarketItem(address,uint256,uint256.details: Function to list a Cardinal NFT on the marketplace

params.nftContract: contract that the NFT was minted on. Only accepts Cardinal NFT contract addresses
params.price: the price of the token in Cardinal Tokens (CRNL)
params.tokenId: the token ID of the NFT on the NFT contract

createMarketSale(address,uint256,uint256.details: Creates the sale of a marketplace item. Transfers ownership of the NFT and sends funds to the seller

params.amountIn: the amount of Cardinal Token the user is supplying to purchase the NFT
params.itemId: the item ID of the NFT on the marketplace
params.nftContract: contract that the NFT was minted on. Only accepts Cardinal NFT contract addresses

fetchItemsCreated(address).details: Returns only items a user has created

params.user: the user to fetch the items created for

returns._0: the list of market items the user has put on the market
the list of market items that haven't been sold

fetchMyNFTs(address).details: Returns only items that a user has purchased

params.user: the user to fetch the NFTs for

returns._0: the list of market items the user owners

fetchUnsoldItemsCreated(address).details: Returns only items a user has created that are currently for sale

params.user: the user to fetch the unsold market items for

returns._0: the list of market items the user has put on the market that are currently for sale

getDefaultListingPrice().details: Gets the listing price for listing an NFT on the marketplace

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setCardinalNFT(address).details: Only owner function to set the reference to the Cardinal NFT contract

params.CardinalNFTAddress: the address for the Cardinal NFT contract

setCardinalToken(address).details: Only owner function to set the reference to the Cardinal Token (CRNL)

params.CardinalTokenAddress: the contract address for the Cardinal Token

setDefaultListingPrice(uint256).details: Only owner function to set the listing price

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

updateBlackList(address,bool).details: Updates the blacklist mapping for a given address

params.blacklisted: a boolean that determines if the given address is being added or removed from the blacklist
params.user: the address that is being added or removed from the blacklist
